5-INGREDIENT HIGH PROTEIN CHICKPEA COOKIE DOUGH🍪 ⁣
Ingredients:⁣
1,5 cups chickpeas, cooked (220 g)⁣
1 cup dates, pitted and soft (150 g)⁣
1/4 cup nut butter (50 g)⁣
2 tbsp oats (15 g)⁣
1 tsp vanilla extract⁣
⁣
optional:⁣
4 tbsp cacao nibs or chocolate chips (25 g)⁣
⁣
Instructions:⁣
If using canned chickpeas, rinse and drain well. Then simply add all the ingredients to a food processor and mix well until smooth. Mix in cacao nibs or chocolate chips, if using. ⁣
⁣
Place in the fridge for 15-20 minutes and enjoy with a spoon. You could also add the cookie dough to your nice cream.⁣
⁣
Note: You may need to soak the dates for 10 minutes in hot water, if they seem too hard. ➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖

KOREAN VEGETABLE PANCAKES 

This Korean vegetable pancake combines a mixed vegetable filling and simple pancake batter for crispy, flavourful veggie pancakes!

Ingredients (For 14 pancakes):
1 cup water
1¼ cup flour
1 tsp salt
1 tsp black pepper
4 small or 2 large carrots
1 zucchini
1/2 onion
Vegetable oil
Soy sauce, to serve

Instructions:
-To a bowl, add flour, salt, black pepper, garlic powder and water whisk until smooth and set aside.
-Cut the veggies into strips and add them to the batter.
-Heat a nonstick griddle or wide skillet. Add a some oil (use at your discretion, depending on your attitude toward oil, how crispy you want the pancakes, and how nonstick you pan is), and when nice and hot, ladle the batter on in 1/3 cup quantities. If you’d like slightly larger pancakes, make that 1/2 cup. 
-If the batter doesn’t spread nicely, add a little more water and whisk in. Cook the pancakes in batches on both sides until golden brown over medium-high heat. 
-Once all the pancakes are cooked, serve warm with soy sauce or any other dipping sauce you like.

Spicy Peanut Noodles are extremely simple to make! A fusion of flavors in a dish that can be prepared in under 10 minutes.

INGREDIENTS (4 servings)
* 12 oz asian noodles
* 1/2 cup soy sauce 
* 2 tbsp Sri racha sauce
* 1/2 cup peanut butter smooth
* 5 cloves garlic minced
* 1 tbsp fresh ginger minced or ginger paste
* To garnish: green onions, crushed peanuts, more Sri racha

INSTRUCTIONS
* Cook noodles according to package instructions.
*  In a small bowl, whisk together the soy sauce, peanut butter, sri racha, garlic and ginger paste until smooth.
* Add noodles and peanut sauce to the pan on low heat and toss well to make sure all the noodles are coated.
* Garnish with Sri racha, crushed peanuts and green onions.
* Enjoy!

Easy Vegan Butterfinger Candy Bars⁣
⁣
Ingredients⁣
* 1 cup chunky peanut butter salted⁣
* 15 Medjool dates⁣
* 3 cups corn flakes⁣
* 2 tbsp maple syrup⁣
* 12 oz non-dairy chocolate chips⁣
⁣
⁣
Instructions⁣
1. Soften the dates in a bowl of hot water for 5 minutes. Meanwhile, crush the corn flakes in a medium sized bowl. Set aside 1/2 cup of corn flakes for garnish. Drain the dates and add them to a food processor along with the peanut butter and maple syrup. Process until smooth then transfer to the bowl of corn flakes. Fold the peanut butter mixture into the corn flakes and stir until even. ⁣
2. Pour the mixture into a loaf tin lined with parchment paper. Use a spatula to level off the top. Freeze for four hours or overnight. When the peanut butter bars are firm, remove them from the tin and cut them into bars. This recipe makes either 8 large candy bars or 16 mini bars. ⁣
3. Melt the chocolate chips in a small sauce pan. Add a few tablespoons of coconut oil or non-dairy milk to thin in out, if desired. Carefully coat each candy bar in chocolate and top with sprinkled corn flake pieces. Freeze again for 30 minutes. Best served right out of the freezer. ➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖

Spaghetti Aglio Olio e Peperoncino (spaghetti with garlic, oil, and chili peppers). It is one of the quickest, most simple pasta dishes you could ever make and one that will become a favorite because it tastes too good!

Ingredients

-300g/10.5oz pasta
-2 cloves of garlic (1 clove per person)
-5-6 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil
-1/2 cup chopped parsley
-chili pepper flakes, to taste
-salt, to taste

Instructions
-Set a large pot of water to boil, generously seasoned with salt, over high heat. Cook the spaghetti according to package instructions, until almost al dente.
-While the pasta is cooking, prepare the sauce by combining the olive oil, garlic and red pepper flakes and in a large skillet. 
-Bring to the stove, over medium low heat, and cook slowly, letting the oil absorb the flavors from the garlic and pepper flakes.
-When the pasta is al dente, transfer it to the skillet with the flavored oil along with 1/2 cup of the pasta water, parsley and salt if needed. -Turn the heat back to medium high and cook, stirring and tossing rapidly until the sauce has thickened/emulsified and coats the pasta. 
-Remove from heat and serve with pepper flakes and parsley.
-Enjoy!

Light and Fluffy Vegan Pancakes

Easy, light and fluffy vegan pancakes made with pantry staples you probably have on hand right now!

Ingredients
for 4 servings
* 1 cup flour (125 g)
* 3 tablespoons sugar
* 1 tablespoon baking powder
* ½ teaspoon salt
* 1 cup non-dairy milk (240 mL)
* 1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar
* 1 teaspoon vanilla extract
* maple syrup, to serve

Preparation
* In a medium bowl or liquid measuring cup, add almond milk, apple cider vinegar, vanilla, and stir to combine.
* In another bowl, add the flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt, and stir to combine.
* Pour the liquid mixture into the dry mixture and whisk until smooth.
* Let batter rest for 10 minutes.
* Pour about ½ cup (65 grams) of batter onto a nonstick pan coated with a bit of oil over medium heat.
* When the top begins to bubble, flip the pancake and cook until golden.
* Serve warm with your favourite toppings (I used berries and maple syrup).
* Enjoy!

These are essential vegan seasonings that every plant-based foodie should have on hand.

CHICKPEA SALAD🥗 

This healthy, summer Chickpea Salad with cucumbers and tomatoes is great for lunch or as a side dish with anything you’re grilling!

Ingredients
* 1 avocado
* ½ fresh lemon
* 1 can chickpeas drained (19 oz)
* ¼ cup red onion sliced
* 2 cups tomatoes sliced
* 2 cups cucumber diced
* ½ cup fresh parsley
* Olive oil, to taste
* Salt, to taste
* Pepper, to taste

Instructions
* Cut veggies into cubes and place in bowl and add the chickpeas.
* Squeeze the juice from ½ lemon over the salad.
* Add remaining salad ingredients and gently toss to combine.
* Refrigerate at least one hour before serving.

Black Bean Burgers🍔

These Bean Burgers are packed with flavour and so satisfying! 
Plus they're super easy to make and made with mostly pantry ingredients.

Ingredients
for 4 servings
* 2 cans black beans, rinsed and drained
* 1 onion, minced
* 3 cloves garlic, minced
* 1 carrots, shredded
* 200g, mushrooms
* ½ cup quick-cook oats (50 g)
* 2 tbsp soy sauce
* 1 tbsp miso paste
* 2 tbsp tomato paste
* 1 tbsp paprika powder
* 1 tbsp garlic powder
* 1 tbsp dried rosemary
* 1 tbsp nutritional yeast (optional)
* salt, to taste
* pepper, to taste
* vegan burger buns

Preparation
* Heat one tablespoon of olive oil in a pan. Combine onions, carrots, mushrooms and garlic and cook until onions are translucent.
* Add, miso paste, tomato paste, paprika powder, garlic powder, dry rosemary, nutritional yeast (optional), salt, pepper and soy sauce and cook on medium heat until the liquid has almost completely evaporated and set aside.
* In a bowl, mash the beans and then add the quick oats along with the and contents of the pan.
* Mix and form patties. 
* Place in freezer for 30 minutes to set (optional).
* Cook patties on a pan coated in a bit of oil over medium heat, flipping halfway.
* Build your burger with your favourite toppings and enjoy!
(The burger I made had onions, tomatoes, arugula and for the sauce I mixed vegan mayo and sri racha)
